  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Description\nWhen a user explicitly specifies an advertised IP (or port) via (`--p2p-advertised-ip` or `--p2p-advertised-port`) Teku should use it regardless of what discv5 PONG responses it receives.\n\nThis is particularly useful when using setups like docker and having some peers within the docker network but wanting discovery to work external to that network (e.g. our test-network).  If there are enough peers inside the docker network, Teku automatically switches to advertising the IP from the internal docker network and so nodes external to docker are unable to use discovery even if ports are correctly forwarded.",
